arch:property.oc:show_val: Material only came from the dry sieve, no flotation. Most of the identifiables are human bones and one distal humerus epiphysis is probably from a wolf given its very large size and young age. NR 2003: Found several bags of flotation, including three all labeled as sample 1. i will keep this separate in case they are supposed to be something else. Sample 1 (flot 3444) >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. This is a smallish sample of smallish but not uniformly tiny pieces, mostly sheep-size. Surface condition is quite variable. There is a piece of human bone. Looks like fill. Sample 1 (flot 3518) >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. it is generally similar to the previous sample 1, with perhaps somewhat better surface condition on average and no human bone. There is some burning and digestion. Looks like fill. Sample 1 (flot 3458) >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded completely. it is similar to the other two samples 1, but smaller. Sample 15 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, recorded as diagnostics and flot frags. This is a much larger sample, fairly similar but with more burning and more diagnostics, some in quite large pieces. Overall, this still looks basically like fill. Last number = 99

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
